<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="301" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[136,787,1570,1850]" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">
<emphasis box="[174,235,1570,1593]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Notes.</emphasis>
– This species is found in Amazonian 
<collectingCountry box="[630,693,1570,1594]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry name="Colombia" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[178,266,1602,1626]" name="Ecuador" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[275,324,1602,1625]" name="Peru" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Peru</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[379,452,1602,1626]" name="Bolivia" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and also is disjunct in 
<collectingCountry box="[685,787,1602,1626]" name="Suriname" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Suriname</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="TAYLOR" box="[146,303,1633,1658]" firstAuthor="TAYLOR" pageId="12" pageNumber="301" pagination="161 - 177" refId="ref27385" refString="TAYLOR, C. M. (2005). Margaritopsis (Rubiaceae, Psychotrieae) in the Neotropics. Syst. Geogr. Pl. 75: 161 - 177." type="journal article" year="2005">TAYLOR, 2005</bibRefCitation>
). DELPRETE &amp; KIRKBRIDE (2015) reported that this species is “widespread in South America”, but it may be restricted to the western Amazon basin. The 
<collectingCountry box="[679,786,1698,1722]" name="Suriname" pageId="12" pageNumber="301">Suriname</collectingCountry>
plants are only known in immature fruit, and are included in this species provisionally. These have smaller inflorescences as well as a markedly disjunct distribution, and probably deserve re-evaluation as to their species identity.
</paragraph>
